# Emphasis formatting
*italic* _italic_
**strong** __strong__
~~strikethrough~~ # some implementations
I need to highlight these ==very important words==. # some implementations
H~2~O # some implementations, Subscript The rendered output allow small '2' in H2O
X^2^  # some implementations, Superscript allow xÂ²

text is the *italic cat's meow*.
text is the _italic cat's meow_.
A*italiccat*meow  # in the middle of a word

I just love **bold text**.
I just love __bold text__.
Love**is**bold # in the middle of a word

This text is ***bold and italic***.
This text is ___bold and italic___.
This text is __*bold and italic*__.
This text is **_bold and italic**_
This is really***very***important text # in the middle of a word

# blockquotes
> first level and paragraph
>> second level or nested block and first paragraph
>
> first level and second paragraph

# lists
# To add another element in a list while preserving the continuity of the list, indent the element four spaces or one tab.
## unordered - use *, +, or -
* Red
* Green

    I need to add another paragraph below the second list item.

* Blue

## ordered
1. First
2. Second
3. Third
4. 1968\. A great year! # If you need to start an unordered list item with a number followed by a period, you can use a backslash (\) to escape the period.

# code - use 4 spaces/1 tab
regular text
        code code code
or:
Use the `printf()` function

