# Escaping Characters
\* Without the backslash, this would be a bullet in an unordered list.
Character Name
\         backslash
`         backtick (see also escaping backticks in code)
*         asterisk
_         underscore
{ }       curly braces
[ ]       brackets
< >       angle brackets
( )       parentheses
#         pound sign
+         plus sign
-         minus sign (hyphen)
.         dot
!         exclamation mark
|         pipe (see also escaping pipe in tables)

# Tables
| Syntax      | Description | Test Text     |
| :---        |    :----:   |          ---: |
| Header      | Title       | Here's this   |
| Paragraph   | Text        | And code `{ my code }`|

    The pipe (|) character using its HTML character code (&#124;).

# footnotes
#
A simple footnote,[^1] and here's a longer one.[^bignote]

[^1]: This is the first footnote.

[^bignote]: Here's one with multiple paragraphs and code.

    Indent paragraphs to include them in the footnote.

    `{ my code }`

    Add as many paragraphs as you like.


# Heading ID

### My Great Heading {#custom-id}

The HTML looks like this:
<h3 id="custom-id">My Great Heading</h3>

# Linking to heading id
[custom ID](#custom-id)
The HTML looks like this:
<a href="#custom-id">Heading IDs</a>

# Task Lists
To create a task list, add dashes (-) and brackets with a space ([ ]) in front of task list items. To select a checkbox, add an x in between the brackets ([x]).

- [x] Write the press release
- [ ] Update the website
- [ ] Contact the media

